.H 2 "Registry Permissions"
.P
.iX "-[" "registry" "objects" "permissions"
.iX "-[" "permissions" "registry objects"
.P
.iX "registry" "table of access permissions to objects" 
Table 41-1 lists the permissions that can be granted for the object types
found in the registry.
.P
.nP
.TB "Permissions for Registry Objects"
.TS 
center,allbox,tab(@);
lB | lB 
cB | lw(3.5i).
Permission@Meaning
_
A@T{
Execute commands that act on replicas (\*Lsec_admin\*O).
T}
a@Modifies authentication information.
c@T{
Modifies ACLs on objects.  All registry ACLs must have one entry that
specifies c (control) permission.
T}
d@Deletes from an object's contents.
D@Deletes an object from the registry.
f@T{
Modifies a principal's, group's, or organization's full name. 
T}
g@Adds a principal to a group.
i@Adds to a object's contents. 
m@Modifies management information.
M@T{
Adds and deletes members from this group or organization.  
To add a member to a group, 
you must also have \*Lg\*O permission for the principal to be added.
T}
n@T{
Modifies the name of a directory, a principal, a group, or an organization.
T}
u@Modifies user information.
r@T{
Views management, authentication, and user information.
T}
t@T{
Tests the group or organization membership of a named principal.
T}
.TE
.H 3 "Management, Authentication, and User Information"
.P
The registry contains three different kinds of information about the objects
in it: management information, authentication information, and user
information.  The specific items of information that are kept for each
object type are summarized in the following subsections. 
.H 4 "Management Information"
.P
...\" .iX "-[" "policies" "management information"
...\" .iX "-[" "properties" "management information"
Management information includes the following categories:
.ML
.LI
For registry policies and properties
.ML
.LI
The account lifespan
.LI
The password minimum length
.LI
The password lifespan
.LI
Whether or not passwords can contain spaces
.LI
Whether or not passwords can consist of all nonalphanumeric
characters
.LI
The password expiration date
.LI
The minimum ticket lifetime
.LI
The default ticket lifetime
.LI
A number that defines the lowest UNIX ID that is supplied
automatically when principals, groups, or organizations are created
.LI
A number that defines the highest number that can be supplied
(either automatically or manually) as a UNIX ID when principals, groups,
or organizations are created
.LI
Whether or not encrypted passwords are displayed (the shadow
password property)
.LE
.LI
...\" .iX "-]" "policies" "management information"
...\" .iX "-]" "properties" "management information"
For principals
.iX "principals" "management information"
.ML
.LI
The account, group, and organization names
.LI
Text string showing the full name of the principal
.LI
Object creation quota for the principal
.LI
Whether the principal can change primary names to aliases
and aliases to primary names
.LI
User Identifier (UID) of the principal
.LI
Unique User Identifier (UUID) of the principal
.LI
The expiration date for the principal's account
.LI
The Account-Valid Flag for the principal's account
.LI
Flags that indicate whether the account is for a principal that 
can act as a client or as a server  
.LE
.LI
For groups
.iX "groups" "management information"
.ML
.LI
Primary name of the group
.LI
Text string showing the full name of the group
.LI
Whether the group's primary name can be changed to an alias
and its aliases to its primary name
.LI
Group Identifier (GID) for the group
.LI
The project list inclusion property
.LI
UUID of the group
.LE
.LI
For organizations
.iX "organizations" "management information"
.ML
.LI
Primary name of the organization
.LI
Whether the organization's primary name can be changed to
an alias and its aliases to its primary name
.LI
Text string showing the full name of the organization
.LI
Organization Identifier (ORGID) for the organization
.LI
UUID of the organization
.LI
The account lifespan
.LI
The password minimum length
.LI
The password lifespan
.LI
The password expiration date
.LI
Whether or not passwords can contain spaces
.LI
Whether or not passwords can consist of all nonalphanumeric
characters
.LE
.LI 
For the \*Lxattrschema\*O object
.ML
.LI
Whether or not the xattrschema can be modified
.LE
.LE
...\" .iX "-[" "policies" "management information"
...\" .iX "-[" "properties" "management information"
.H 4 "Authentication Information"
.P
.iX "-[" "authentication policies"
Authentication information includes the following categories:
.iX "policies" "authentication information"
.iX "properties" "authentication information"
.ML
.LI
For registry policies and properties
.ML
.LI
The maximum ticket lifetime
.LI
The maximum time for which tickets can be renewed
.LE
.LI
For principals
.iX "principals" "authentication information"
.ML
.LI
The maximum ticket lifetime for the principal's account
.LI
The maximum time for which tickets that are issued to the principal's
account can be renewed
.LI
The date and time that the principal's account was last changed (Good
Since Date)
.LI
The date and time that the principal's account was enabled (Last Changed Date)
.LI
The creator of the principal's account and account creation date
.LI
Description of the account's use
.LI
Whether the principal's account can be issued postdated
tickets, forwardable tickets, renewable tickets, or proxiable tickets
.LI
Whether the DCE Authentication Service can issue tickets to
the principal's account based on ticket-granting ticket authorization
or whether principals must obtain tickets directly for the service
.LI
Whether the principal's account can be issued duplicate
session keys
.LE
.LE
.iX "-]" "authentication policies"
.H 4 "User Information"
.P
.iX "-[" "user information"
User information includes the following information pertaining to
a principal's account:
.ML
.LI
Password
.LI
Home directory
.LI
Miscellaneous information (GECOS information)
.LI
Login shell
.LI
Password-Valid Flag
.LE 
.iX "-]" "user information"
.H 3 "Permission Required to Create Principals, Groups, or Organizations"
.P
.iX "-[" "principals" "adding to registry"
.iX "-[" "groups" "adding to registry"
.iX "-[" "organizations" "adding to registry"
Figure 41-2 shows the permission that is required to create principals, 
groups, or organizations. 
.P
.FG "Permission Required to Create Principals, Groups, or Organizations"
.nL
.pI ../security/security/figures/13_access_20.ps 0 0 1
.sp .5
.P
To create a principal, group, or organization, you must have
\*Li\*O permission on the directory in which you create the principal,
group, or organization.  For example, to create the principal 
\*Lpreludes/villa/lobos\*O, you must have \*Li\*O on \*Lvilla\*O. 
.iX "-]" "principals" "adding to registry"
.iX "-]" "groups" "adding to registry"
.iX "-]" "organizations" "adding to registry"
.H 3 "Permissions Required to Delete Principals, Group, or Organizations"
.P
.iX "-[" "principals" "deleting"
.iX "-[" "groups" "deleting"
.iX "-[" "organizations" "deleting" 
Figure 41-3 shows the permissions that are required to delete principals, 
groups, or organizations.
.P
.FG "Permissions Required to Delete Principals, Groups, or Organizations \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ "
.nL
.pI ../security/security/figures/13_access_30.ps 0 0 1
.sp .5
.P
To delete principals, groups, or organizations, you must have the
following permissions:
.ML
.LI
The \*Ld\*O permission on the directory in which the
principal to be deleted exists 
.LI
The \*LrD\*O permission on the principal, group, or
organization to be deleted
.LE
.P
For example, to delete the principal \*Lpreludes/villa/lobos\*O,
you must have the \*Ld\*O permission for the \*Lpreludes/villa \*Odirectory,
and \*LrD\*O permissions for the principal \*Lpreludes/villa/lobos\*O. 
.iX "-]" "principals" "deleting"
.iX "-]" "groups" "deleting"
.iX "-]" "organizations" "deleting"
.H 3 "Permissions Required to Add Accounts"
.P
.iX "-[" "accounts" "creating"
.zA "def, 13575,R1.2.2,removed rgy_edit"
When you add accounts, by using the \*Luser create\*O  command, \*Ldcecp\*O 
adds the principal to the group or organization
that is named in the account, if the principal is not already a member of 
the group and/or organization.  For this reason, the permissions that
are required to add an account may include the permissions 
that are required to add a member to a group or organization.  The
following topics are covered in the discussion of the permissions
required to add accounts:
.zZ "def, 13575,R1.2.2,removed rgy_edit"
.ML
.LI
.ne 3
The permissions that are required to add an account and at the same time
add the principal as a member of the group and organization that is
named in the account.  (See Section 41.2.4.1.)
.LI
The permissions that are required to add an account for which the principal
is already a member of the named group and organization.  (See Section
41.2.4.2.)
.LI
The permissions that are
required to add an account and add the principal only to the group that is
named in the account (because the principal is already a member of 
the organization).  (See Section 41.2.4.3.)
.LI 
The permissions that are
required to add an account and add the principal only to the 
organization that is
named in the account (because the principal is already a member 
of the group).  (See Section 41.2.4.4.)
.LE 
.H 4 "Adding an Account and the Account Principal to the Group and Organization"
.P
Figure 41-4 shows the 
permissions required to add an account and the account 
principals to the group or organization.
.P
.FG "Permissions Required to Add an Account and the Account Principal to the Group and Organization" 
.nL
.pI ../security/security/figures/13_access_40.ps 0 0 1
.sp .5
.P
To add an account and add the account's principal to the group and the 
organization named in the account automatically, you must have the following 
permissions:
.ML
.LI
The \*Lmaug\*O permissions on the account's principal
.LI
The \*LtM\*O permissions on the group that is named in the account
.LI
The \*LrtM\*O permissions on the organization that is named in the account
.LI
The \*Lr\*O permission on the registry \*Lpolicy\*O object
.LE
.P
For example, to create an account for the principal 
\*Lpreludes/villa/lobos\*O associated with the group \*Lcomposers\*O and the 
organization \*Lpianists\*O, you must have the following permissions:
.ML
.LI
The \*Lmaug\*O permissions on \*Lpreludes/villa/lobos\*O 
.LI
The \*LtM\*O permissions on the group \*Lcomposers\*O
.LI 
The \*LrtM\*O permissions on the organization \*Lpianists\*O 
.LI
The \*Lr\*O permission on the registry \*Lpolicy\*O object 
.LE
.nL
.H 4 "Adding an Account for Which the Principal is Already a Member of the Group and Organization"
.P
Figure 41-5 shows the permissions that
are required to add an account for which the principal is 
already a member of the group or organization.
.P
.FG "Adding an Account For Which the Principal Is Already a Member of the Group and Organization"
.nL
.pI ../security/security/figures/13_access_41.ps 0 0 1
.sp .5
.P
To add an account that does not require adding the account's 
principal to the group and the organization 
named in the account, you must have the following permissions:
.ML
.LI
The \*Lmau\*O permissions on the account principal
.LI
At least one permission of any kind on the group 
that is named in the account
.LI
The \*Lr\*O permission on the organization that is named in the account
.LI
The \*Lr\*O permission on the registry \*Lpolicy\*O object
.LE
