.H 3 "Permissions Required by Slave Replicas"
.iX "replica" "slave permissions (security"
In order to initialize and function properly, 
slave replicas must have the \*Li\*O, \*Lm\*O, and 
\*LI\*O permissions for the \*Lreplist\*O object (\*L/.:/sec/replist\*O).  
A slave server runs under the indentity of the machine on which 
it runs.  A machine name is the local host principal name in the following
form:
.iS
host/\*Vhostname\*O/\*Lself\*O
.iE
.P
The required ACL entry is added when the \*Ldce_config\*O tool 
initially configures the DCE cell's security server and when 
you use the tool to create new slave replicas.  
The entry has the following form:
.iS
user:host/\*Vhostname\*O/\*Lself:imI\*O
