.H 2 "Registry ACL Manager"
.P
.iX "-[" "ACL manager" "for registry database"
The registry ACL manager consists of five manager types, which are 
used to handle different ACL semantics that are 
required by the five types of objects in the
registry.  For example, the principal ACL manager
type controls the ACLs on all \*Lprincipal\*O objects in the registry. 
Because \*Lgroup\*O objects require a set of permissions 
that are different than those of a \*Lprincipal\*O object, 
there is a separate group ACL manager
type that controls the ACLs on \*Lgroup\*O objects.
.P
Not all permissions nor all ACL entry types are valid for each 
ACL manager.  Table 41-2 summarizes the valid and invalid permissions
and the invalid ACL entry types for each ACL manager.
.P
